gw.plugin.contact

Interface ContactResult

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DuplicateContactResult

    public interface ContactResult
    A ContactResult represents a set of basic contact fields returned from an external Contact Management System or Address Book. A ContactResult has methods to get all the basic fields it needs to display in the UI, as well as a few utility methods to assist in converting the result into a real Contact in PolicyCenter.

    • Method Detail

      • convertToContact

        Contact convertToContact(ContactCreator creator)
        Converts this ContactResult into an actual Contact in the given bundle
        Parameters:
        creator - a ContactCreator that will load an existing Contact or create a new one as appropriate
        Returns:
        A Contact representing this ContactResult. If a Contact with the same AddressBookUID exists locally, it will be loaded into the given bundle with field values from the external system. If no Contact exists in PolicyCenter with the given AddressBookUID, a new Contact is minted in the given bundle with field values from the external system.
